d-indian-student-dies-of-heart-attack-in-us-a-day-after-celebrating-graduation-walk/articleshow/130960365.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-08T18:09:53+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130960424,imgsize-113664.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[South America’s Champions League match stopped less than 2 mins in after fans started burning stadium sections]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130959177.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Chaos engulfed a Copa Libertadores clash between CR Flamengo and Independiente Medellín after violent fan protests forced the match to be abandoned minutes after kick-off. Fires, pitch invasion attempts and attacks on journalists highlighted deep unrest surrounding Medellín’s ownership, with Flamengo now expected to receive a 3-0 victory under CONMEBOL regulations.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/international-sports/south-americas-champions-league-match-stopped-less-than-2-mins-in-after-fans-started-burning-stadium-sections/articleshow/130959177.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/international-sports/south-americas-champions-league-match-stopped-less-than-2-mins-in-after-fans-started-burning-stadium-sections/articleshow/130959177.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-08T17:43:41+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Sports Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130959571,imgsize-187632.cms"/></item></channel></rss>